.TH man 1 "22 Apr 2024" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- A simple shell created in C for interacting with a Linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
 The shell is executed by typing ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell is a UNIX term for the interactive user interface with an operating system. The shell is the layer of programming that understands
and executes the commands a user enters. In some systems, the shell is called a command interpreter. A shell usually implies an interface
with a command syntax 

.B Overview
.br
The simple shell is a lightweight command-line interpreter that allows users to execute basic commands in a Linux environment. It reads commands from the standard input or from a file, interprets them, and executes them. It is designed to be simple and easy to use, making it suitable for basic scripting and interactive use.

.SH Return Value

The simple shell returns 0 upon successful execution of a command. Any other number indicates a failure or error.

.SH PATH

The simple shell searches for executables in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable. If an executable is found, it is executed; otherwise, an error message is displayed.

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options are specified after the main command followed by a space and a '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

To list the contents of a directory: $ ls.

.SH BUGS
A single space is required after each argument.

.SH AUTHOR
Ivan Pacheco, Sebastian Meneses Salazar.
